The association constant for subunits to tetramer in the presence of $X$ is therefore
$$K S_{0}^{*}=\frac{[H b]+[H b X]}{[s]^{4}}=K S_{0}\left(1+B_{0} x\right) .$$

Similarly $K S_{4}^{*}=K S_{4}\left(1+B_{4} x\right)$ where $B_{4}$ is the association constant of $X$ to $H b\left(\mathrm{O}_{2}\right)_{4}$. If $x$ is buffered, or effectively constant because it is in large excess, $x$ is the same at all stages of ligation. The following discussion assumes this is the case. From (2.15), if $\ln p_{m x}$ denotes the value in the presence of $X$ and $\ln p_{m}$ the value in its absence
$$\begin{aligned}
\ln p_{m x} & =\ln p_{s}+\frac{1}{4} \ln \frac{K S_{0}\left(1+B_{0} x\right)}{K S_{4}\left(1+B_{4} x\right)} \\
\ln p_{m} & =\ln p_{s}+\frac{1}{4} \ln \frac{K S_{0}}{K S_{4}} \text { from (2.15), }
\end{aligned}$$
