This equation shows that if $x$ is buffered, $\log p_{m x}$ depends only on the binding constants of $X$ to fully oxygenated and deoxygenated haemoglobin and is independent of the binding of $X$ to intermediate structures.

The expression for release of ligand $X$. The Adair constants for oxygen binding in the presence of $X$ will be given by eq. (2.16), substituting the altered values of $K S_{i}^{*}$
$$\begin{aligned}
\log A_{i x}^{\prime} & =\log A_{s}+\log \left[K S_{i} \times \phi_{i}(x)\right]-\log \left[K S_{i-1} \times \phi_{i-1}(x)\right] \\
& =\log A_{i}^{\prime}+\log \phi_{i}(x)-\log \phi_{i-1}(x)
\end{aligned}$$
