$$X_{i}=\frac{d \log \phi_{i}(x)}{d \log x}$$

Therefore the number of molecules of $X$ released at each stage of oxygenation,
$$\begin{aligned}
\Delta X_{i} & =X_{i-1}-X_{i} \\
& =\frac{d \log \phi_{i-1}(x)}{d \log x}-\frac{d \log \phi_{i}(x)}{d \log x}
\end{aligned}$$

